doc.after: Dream time also dreamtime dream time world dawn is a term for the animist framework and symbol system of Australian Aboriginal mythology introduced by A P Elkin in 1938 and popularized by William Edward Hanley Stanner and others from the 1970s for a concept of time out of time or everywhen inhabited by ancestral figures often of heroic proportions or with supernatural abilities but not considered gods as they do not control the material world and are not worshipped 1
